 like young and grey ice, typically less\nthan 30 cm, were not resolved. The ARC MFC model's wave dissipation rate has a\nsea ice thickness dependence, and therefore, it overestimates wave dissipation\nin thin ice cover; sea ice forcing that can resolve the thin thickness\ndistribution is needed to improve the predictability. This study provides an\nobservational insight into better predictions of waves in marginal ice zones\nwhen new ice forms.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 2 Feb 2023 11:10:57 GMT"}],"update_date":"2023-02-07"}
